The paper deals with automated planning for robotic spatial extrusion, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses a CSP encoding for the planning problem, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves 3D truss structures, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with motion planning, which is a common problem in control systems (cs.SY).
